The paper deals with the algorithmic aspects of matroids, which are combinatorial objects studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from logic (cs.LO) and computational complexity (cs.CC) to analyze the decidability of first order logic properties in matroids. Finally, the paper discusses the problem of finding circuits in matroids, which is related to computational geometry (cs.CG).
